<h2>Elastos&nbsp;2.0 Installation And Use</h2>

    <h3>About Elastos&nbsp;2.0</h3>

        <p>Elastos&nbsp;2.0 is the second officially released version of Elastos embedded operating system. This CD provides Elastos&nbsp;2.0 executable that runs on Intel&nbsp;X86 series and its compatible CPU. User can run Elastos operating system on normal IBM&nbsp;PC-AT compatible machine, including PC compatible industrial machine, single board computer etc. This document introduces only to IBM&nbsp;PC-AT compatible hardware platform installation and use.If you have other requests please contact Koretide Corp.</p>

    <h3>Preparation before Elastos&nbsp;2.0 installation</h3>

        <p>Need to prepare the following development environment: </p>
        <table>
          <thead>
            <td align="center" nowrap>¡¡</td>
            <td align="center">Hardware</td>
            <td align="center">Software</td>
            <td align="center">Remarks</td>
          </thead>
          <tr>
            <td nowrap>Host</td>
            <td>1 PC</td>
            <td>Fits requirement for Elastos.SDK installation and already installed Elastos.SDK.</td>
            <td>Used for host development.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td nowrap>Target machine</td>
            <td>IBM PC-AT compatible hardware platform (486 or above CPU, 8MB or above RAM)</td>
            <td>N/A</td>
            <td>Run Elastos&nbsp;2.0 target machine, PC or PC compatible industrial control machine and single board computer.</td>
          </tr>
        </table>

        <p>Corresponds to different boot method and requires the hardware platform to have the following condition: </p>
        <table>
          <thead>
            <td align="center" nowrap>Boot method</td>
            <td align="center">Host</td>
            <td align="center">Target machine</td>
          </thead>
          <tr>
            <td nowrap>Hard disk start</td>
            <td>Floppy drive, COM1 port.</td>
            <td>Floppy drive, hard drive (7MB and above), COM1 port, installation of DOS&nbsp;6.0 and above.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td nowrap>Network startup</td>
            <td>Floppy drive, COM1 port, network card, install TFTPD service.</td>
            <td>Floppy drive, COM1 port, RTL8139 series network card.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td nowrap>Flash bootup</td>
            <td>Not in this documentation.</td>
            <td>¡¡</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td nowrap>Diskless startup</td>
            <td>Not in this documentation.</td>
            <td>¡¡</td>
          </tr>
        </table>

        <ol><b>Remarks: </b>
            <li>Target machine needs to connect to monitor,keyboard. For Elastos&nbsp;2.0 supported video card please see <a class="style1" href="../../ddk/ddk_environment/support_list.htm">driver list</a> for reference.
            <li>Needs to prepare necessary blank floppy, serial cable and network cable.
            <li>Network startup needs to configure TFTPD service, For user to start service from network,please contact Koretide Corp.
            <li>Flash start and diskless start needs more technical knowledge, which is not discussed in details in this documentation.If users need the documentation please contact Koretide Corp.
        </ol>

